Baby capybaras, known as pups, are born well-developed and can see, walk, and swim almost immediately after birth. They usually weigh about 2-3 pounds and are nursed by their mother and other females in the group. Capybara pups are highly social and stay close to the group, learning to forage and communicate through vocalizations. They grow rapidly and begin eating grass within a week, although they continue nursing for about 16 weeks.

TOKYO CAPYBARA CAFEð¯ðµ

Many of Japan's animal cafes are very controversial and their track records aren't great. So you can imagine my excitement when I found an animal cafe with just two animals, customers are limited to 10 at a time for specific time slots and the animals are cabybaras...

I can't tell you how much I've wanted to see a Capybara in real life, and these two are called Kohaku and Pisuke - they're two pampered cappys and I fell in love.

The fee is 1250 yen for 30 minutes in the cafe but you do need to go early in the morning for a slot or to put your name on the list for later in the day.

you can also buy snacks for the Capybara for 330 yen.

Probably one of my favourite experiences in Tokyo ð¯ðµ
